Did you know you can rate our content?

Posted by raymondlewallen on April 6, 2005

I don’t know if anybody notice or not, but you can now rate the
content of an individual blog post.  If you are reading this from
our blog home page, then you can’t see links to
leave comments or rate a post.  So go ahead, to start, click on
the title of this blog post up above or click here to take you into my blog and we’ll
continue this………..

Welcome back, and welcome to my blog, if you clicked the link

At the bottom of this post, you will see links that say “Post a
Comment”, “Rate”, “Track this post”.  I want to tell you about the
“Rate”.  If you don’t feel as though you have the time or the
energy to leave a comment telling us how good looking we are or that we
don’t know what we’re talking about, the “Rate” feature is a 2 step
process that most of you can do in under 1 second.

When you click “Rate”, you get a dropdown of 6 choices: Terrible,
Poor, Fair, Average, Good, Excellent.  I personally think the list
is backwards, and they should be good to bad from top to bottom so that
you don’t have to go to the bottom of the list to rate our blog posts
(j/k).  Either way, just click on the link (not the stars) that
reflects how you feel about the post you are reading.  Completely
anonymous, no need to take time to leave feedback, just a quick 1–2
click and you’re done!  It is a great, simple and fast way to
leave us feedback to help us make better decisions about what we talk
about.

Update: It appears as though this does NOT work for anonymous users, althought when you rate a post as a user it remains anonymous who ranked what post at what ranking. Click here to register, its free!
